dwithadditionalreporting.AmidprolongedsilencefromNorthKoreanstatemediaonthewhereaboutsofleaderKimJongUn,socialmediaplatformshavefilledtheinformationvacuumbyspreadingandamplifyingrumors,anNKNewsanalysishasfound.InthedayssinceanApril21articleontheSeoul-basedwebsiteDailyNKreportedthatKimwasrecoveringfromacardiovascularprocedure,Twitter—where#KIMJONGUNDEADwasthetop-trendingtopicovertheweekend—textmessagingapps,andChina’sWeibohavechurnedoutafloodofsensationalnewsstoriesabouttheDPRKleader.Therumorscontainvividtalespackedwithcinematicdetail:Kimclutchinghisheartwhenhecollapsedontheground;acrowdof50Chinesedoctorsrushingintotheoperatingroomexactlyeightminutesafterhisbypasssurgeryfailed.SohowdidtheKimJongUnhealthrumormillgofromasimplereportofaheartproceduretostoriesofKimJongUn’sdeathandasuccessioncrisisinNorthKorea?NKNewstookalookatsomeofthewildest—andmostpervasive—claimsabouttheDPRKleader’shealth.THEREPORTTHATSTARTEDITALLTheDailyNKarticle’sclaimwasstraightforward:Kimhadundergonea“cardiovascularprocedure”onApril12andwasrecoveringatHyangsanMedicalCenter,reportedlytheKimfamily’spersonalhospital.Thatarticlecited“NorthKoreansources,”butacorrectionissuedthesameday—afterthearticle’sviralreceptiononline—clarifiedthattheinformationhadcomefromonlya“singleDailyNKsource”insidetheDPRK.MostofthemedicalstaffreturnedtoPyongyangonApril19afterKim’shealthimproved,thearticlesaid,but“afewremainandarecontinuingtomonitorhisrecovery.”ThearticlewaspickedupinEnglishbyReutersandthenCNNthesameday—andwithinhourshadbecomeoneofthebiggeststoriesintheworld.TheCNNarticleadditionallyclaimedthatU.S.intelligencewasmonitoringreportsthatKimwasin“gravedanger”aftersurgery.ButCNN’sarticlealsochangedafterpublication:theoriginalheadlineread,“U.S.Source:NorthKoreanleaderingravedangeraftersurgery.”Itwaseventuallychangedtothemoretentative“U.S.monitoringintelligencethatNorthKoreanleaderisingravedangeraftersurgery.”Bythen,wordthatKimJongUnmaybeincapacitated,orevendead,wasalreadyspreadingaroundtheworld.Inasignofjusthowquickl