adlineread,“U.S.Source:NorthKoreanleaderingravedangeraftersurgery.”Itwaseventuallychangedtothemoretentative“U.S.monitoringintelligencethatNorthKoreanleaderisingravedangeraftersurgery.”Bythen,wordthatKimJongUnmaybeincapacitated,orevendead,wasalreadyspreadingaroundtheworld.Inasignofjusthowquicklythesekindsofrumorscanspread,oneHongKongmediaexecutive,QinFeng,postedamessageonWeibocontainingjusttwocandleemojis.Forsome,themessage—nowdeleted—wasproofenoughthatKimhaddied.“IstheKimnewsreal?QinFengpostedcandlesonWeibo,”askedoneChinese-languageuseronTwitter.“Let’sseehowmanyhoursit’llbeuntiltheofficialannouncement,”QinsaidinalongerWeibopostthatwasalsodeleted.“Ineverpostfakeinformation.”QinisthenieceofformerChineseforeignministerLiZhaoxing.TheChinese-languageWorldJournalreferredtoQinFeng’sWeibopostsasacrediblesignthatKimhadreallydied,andtheDutchnewspaperDeTelegraafcitedthe“topHongKongSatelliteTelevisionfigure’s”claimsaswell.Insomeforeignpublications,asifplayingagameoftelephone,QinFengbecameanunidentified“HongKongsource.”TherumoraboutKimJongUn’sdeath,however,stayedthesame.FALSEIMAGESSomeoutletsturnedtomorestraightforwardvideoandphotomanipulations.WidelysharedfakevideosandimageswithJapanesesubtitlesalsoappeartoshowKimJongUn’sfuneraldisplay,withNorthKorea’sfamousnewsannouncerRiChunHeedressedinablackhanbokannouncingKim’sdeath.Onevideo,publishedonApril21andwithover895,928viewsasofTuesday,isamanipulatedversionofaJapanesetelevisionspotthatairedwhenformerNorthKoreanleaderKimJongIl—KimJongUn’sfather—diedin2011.Themanipulatedvideocontainsseveralglaringartefactsofitsorigin,includingRiChunHee’soriginalKoreanaudioannouncingKimJongIl’sdeath.Inasignofjusthowquicklythesekindsofrumorscanspread,oneHongKongmediaexecutive,QinFeng,postedamessageonWeibocontainingjusttwocandleemojis.Forsome,themessage—nowdeleted—wasproofenoughthatKimhaddied.“IstheKimnewsreal?QinFengpostedcandlesonWeibo,”askedoneChinese-languageuseronTwitter.“Let’sseehowmanyhoursit’llbeuntiltheofficialannouncement,”QinsaidinalongerWeibo