canChinese-languagenewssiteUSOCCTN(美国海外电视网)saidthatKimJongUnhadbeentransferredfromahospitalinWonsantoahospitalinPyongyang—andthathehadsufferedacerebralhemorrhagetendaysbefore.Becauseofhisincapacitatedstate,thearticlesaid,hisuncleKimPyongIl—thebrotherofKimJongIl—wastakingchargeofthecountry.KimYoJong—KimJongUn’ssister—wasputunderhousearrest,thearticlealsosaid.Thearticle’scontentshavebeenrepackagedandcirculatedviatext.Anallegedscreengrabofachatlogcites“anarticle”asitssource,butdoesnotspecifyfromwhere.MAKINGSENSEOFTHEMADNESSLookingatthearrayoftherumorsoutthere—andthesheerscaleofinterestinthestory—it’sclearthatreportsofKimJongUn’sillhealthhavesparkedglobalinterestinNorthKoreafollowingayearinwhichPyongyanghadlargelyfallentothewayside.Andwhat’salsoclearisthedesperateneedtoseparatefactfromfiction,aswellasthepowerofotherwise-reputablenewsoutletstospreadmisinformationandgossip.ButwithnetizenshavingdeclaredthattheNorthKoreanleaderisdead,alive,inacoma,orevenabductedbyaliens,rumorslikelywillpersistuntilKimJongUnappearsinpublicagain.TheUSismonitoringintelligencethatsuggestsNorthKorea'sleader,KimJongUn,isingravedangerafterundergoingaprevioussurgery,accordingtoaUSofficialwithdirectknowledge.AsecondsourcefamiliarwiththeintelligencetoldCNNthattheUShasbeencloselymonitoringreportsonKim'shealth.Kimrecentlymissedthecelebrationofhisgrandfather'sbirthdayonApril15,whichraisedspeculationabouthiswell-being.Hehadbeenseenfourdaysbeforethatatagovernmentmeeting.AnotherUSofficialtoldCNNMondaythattheconcernsaboutKim'shealtharecrediblebuttheseverityishardtoassess.NationalSecurityAdviserRobertO'BriensaidtheUSis"keepingacloseeye"onreportsaboutKim'shealth."We'remonitoringthesereportsveryclosely,"O'BriensaidduringaninterviewwithFoxNewsTuesday."Asyouknow,NorthKoreaisaveryclosedsociety,"hesaid.LateronTuesday,aUSdefenseofficialsaidthattheUSmilitaryassessmentisthatwhiletheyareexaminingreportsregardingKim'spoorhealth,theevidenceatthispointdoesnotsuggestheisincapacitated.DailyNK,anonlinenewspaperbasedinSouthK